<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In papermaking, an alternate term for <a title="Sizing" href="Sizing">sizing</a>. See <a title="Sizing" href="Sizing">Sizing</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In ink manufacturing, <em>size</em> is an ink that retains a considerable degree of <a title="Tack" href="Tack">tack</a>, or stickiness, after it has dried, allowing for the application of <a title="metallic powder" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/metallic_powder">metallic powder</a> (or other types of powders) to provide an additional metallic luster to the printing (a process called <a title="Bronze Dusting" href="Bronze_Dusting">bronze dusting</a>). 
</p>
<p id="l5">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, <em>size</em> is a mixture (often containing <a title="Albumen" href="Albumen">albumen</a>) used in <a title="Gilding" href="Gilding">gilding</a> or <a title="Foil Stamping" href="Foil_Stamping">foil stamping</a> to facilitate the adhesion of the <a title="Gold Leaf" href="Gold_Leaf">gold leaf</a> to the book cover. 
</p>
<div style="clear: both;"></div></div>


